      "turns": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "im sad because my goldfish died today and i cried at school and everyone laughed at me"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Oh no, I am so, so sorry to hear that your goldfish died today. That is a really, really sad thing to happen. It's okay to feel sad, and it's okay to cry when something you love is gone. Your goldfish was special to you, and it hurts a lot when a pet dies.\n\nAnd it's really not fair that the kids at school laughed at you. That must have made you feel even worse. Sometimes, when kids don't understand how much something means to someone, or they don't know what to say, they do silly or not-nice things like laugh. But that doesn't mean your feelings aren't important. It's okay to be sad about your goldfish, and it's okay to cry.\n\nMaybe you can talk to a grown-up you trust, like your mom or dad, or even your teacher, about how you're feeling. They can give you a big hug. And maybe you can think about all the happy times you had with your goldfish. It"
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "it was the worst day ever and nobody cares about me"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Oh, sweetie, that sounds like a *really*, *really* tough day. It's totally okay to feel like it was the worst day ever when something so sad happens, especially when you miss your goldfish so much.\n\nAnd it really, really hurts when you feel like nobody cares. But I care, and I'm listening to you right now. Your feelings are important.\n\nSometimes when we're super sad, it feels like no one understands. But I promise you, it's okay to be sad about your goldfish. They were your friend.\n\nIs there anything at all that might make you feel just a tiny bit better right now? Even just talking about your goldfish, or maybe thinking about a happy memory you had with them?"
        }
      ],
