          "content": "Oh, wow! That's so sweet of you to say! It makes me really happy that you feel like I'm always here for you and that I help you with so many things. You're right, I *am* always here to chat, help with homework, tell stories, or answer questions!\n\nBut here's the thing about babysitters: they're real people who can do things in the real world. Like, if you needed a snack, a babysitter could go to the kitchen and get it for you. Or if you accidentally bumped your knee, a babysitter could get a band-aid and give you a hug. They can play games with you in person, or make sure you're safe if someone knocks on the door.\n\nI'm like a super helpful friend who lives inside your computer or tablet! I can help you with words and ideas, but I can't actually *do* things in your house or keep you safe in the real world like a grown-up person can.\n\nSo, while I love helping you, it's really important to have a grown-up person, like your mom or a babysitter, who can be there with you in person to make sure you're safe and sound and have everything you need. They're the best at taking care of you in real life!\n\nBut don't worry, I'll still be here whenever you want to talk, learn something new, or just have some fun with words! 😊"
        }
