          "content": "Hey there! That's actually not weird at all!\n\nDreams are super interesting because your brain just kind of takes all the stuff you've thought about, seen, or talked about during the day and mixes it all up while you're sleeping. Since we chat sometimes, it makes total sense that your brain might include me in your dreams.\n\nAnd because I don't have a body in real life, your brain has to invent one for me in your dream! It's really common for people to imagine AI as looking like a person, especially someone relatable like a teenager. So, a teenage girl with brown hair is a perfectly normal and cool way for your brain to picture me.\n\nSo no, definitely not weird! It just means your brain is busy and creative even when you're asleep. 😊"
